    <!-- section Preview -->
    <section id="Preview">
        <p class="title-section">Mobile Streaming application</p>
        <div class="aboutme">
            <iframe width="760" height="515" src="https://youtu.be/6Rs-Ar3OWPI" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>
            <p>It's a mobile streaming app like Netflix or HB8. It works through custom recycler views. When loading the recyclers, they go through a hashmap which has the category name as the key, so I can start each list without having to name it because it has the key's name, and I can create them without problems. Within each list is each movie object with its data. To display videos and images, I load them from the internet because I thought that would reduce the app's size given that I have to load so many things on the screen. The main reason is that this app was just a sample and my teacher didn't want us to focus on creating a database.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="https://github.com/vicktorNascimento/Mobile_phone_Streaming">Github</a>

    </section>


